{"word":"σῖτος","slug":"σῖτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>σῖτος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ orig.\">orig.</a> uncertain; ‘grain of any kind’] in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> generally <b>wheat</b> (also termed ‘corn’) may be inferred <b><a href='B:470 3:12'>Mt 3:12</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> The rare <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pl.\">pl.</a> <el>τὰ σῖτα</el> <b><a href='B:510 7:12'>Ac 7:12</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> refers in general to provisions; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σιτίον\">σιτίον</a></el>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σιτομέτριον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Σιχάρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}